Here's a complete implementation:

### XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="Auto,*" ColumnSpacing="12">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found." HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

### ViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? selectedItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;

        await _nav.GoToAsync(nameof(DetailPage), new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", SelectedItem }
        });

        // Clear selection so the same item can be re-selected later
        SelectedItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // Must set false to hide the spinner
        }
    }
}
```

### Key binding points

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `SelectedItem` | `Item? SelectedItem` | **TwoWay** ‚ÄĒ set to `null` after navigation to allow re-selection |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on selection; triggers navigation |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Fires on pull-to-refresh |
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `bool IsRefreshing` | Set `false` when done to hide spinner |
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | Use `ObservableCollection`, never `List<T>` |

### Important details

- **`RefreshView` wraps `CollectionView`** ‚ÄĒ pull-to-refresh is not built into `CollectionView` itself.
- **Always set `IsRefreshing = false`** in a `finally` block so the spinner hides even on errors.
- **Clear `SelectedItem` after navigating** so the user can tap the same item again.
- **Set `x:DataType`** on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings and build-time safety.
- This uses the **MVVM Community Toolkit** (`[ObservableProperty]`, `[RelayCommand]`) to reduce boilerplate.
